  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insurance Under $50,000</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Panama specifically requires $50,000 minimum coverage. Some budget travel insurance plans don't meet this. Verify your certificate shows at least $50,000 in medical coverage before applying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing COVID Coverage</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Panama still requires COVID-19 coverage as part of the health insurance requirement. Many standard policies include this now, but confirm it's explicitly stated on your certificate.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Panama City Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Panama City is more expensive than most Latin American capitals—closer to Miami pricing. Budget $2,500+/month for comfortable living, or consider basing in Boquete/Pedasi.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Not Registering Within 30 Days</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">After arrival, you must register with immigration within 30 days. Missing this deadline can complicate your status. Put it on your calendar.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Waiting Too Long to Extend</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply for your 9-month extension before your initial visa expires—not after. Processing takes time, and an expired visa creates complications.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

