  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is my foreign income really tax-free?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. Panama uses territorial taxation—you only pay taxes on Panama-sourced income. Remote work income from foreign companies is not taxed. This is one of Panama's biggest draws for digital nomads earning in USD.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I open a bank account?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, but it's become more difficult in recent years. As a digital nomad visa holder, you can open accounts, but banks require substantial documentation. Having a lawyer or fixer helps. Some nomads use fintech alternatives initially.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What happens after 18 months?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The digital nomad visa is non-renewable beyond 18 months. Options include: leaving and applying for a new one, transitioning to a different visa (like Friendly Nations), or using tourist status while exploring other residency paths.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Panama City safe?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Generally yes, especially in expat-friendly areas like Punta Pacifica, Casco Viejo, and Costa del Este. Use normal urban precautions. Some neighborhoods should be avoided. Overall, it's safer than many Latin American capitals.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Panama City has excellent internet—fiber is widely available in modern buildings with speeds of 100+ Mbps. Boquete and beach towns have decent but slower internet. Always verify before committing to accommodation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need a lawyer?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Not required for the digital nomad visa—the online process is straightforward. However, a lawyer ($500-1,500) can help if you want to expedite the process, handle complications, or explore longer-term residency options.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

